Whether a point lies inside the mesh division delineated by the MeshDivision object.

Parameters

324 _current_direction == FROM_MULTIAPP ? (to_problem.getUserObjectBase(to_postprocessor))
325 : (from_problem->getUserObjectBase(from_postprocessor)));
326 auto & to_solution = to_var.sys().solution();
327 auto & to_mesh = to_problem.mesh().getMesh();
328 bool is_nodal = to_sys.variable_type(var_num).family == LAGRANGE;
329 if (is_nodal)
330 {
331 for (const auto & node : to_mesh.local_node_ptr_range())
332 {
333 // Skip this node if the variable has no dofs at it.
334 if (node->n_dofs(sys_num, var_num) < 1)
335 continue;
336
337 Real scale = 1;
338 if (_current_direction == FROM_MULTIAPP)
339 {
340 auto ii = pps.nearestPointIndex(*node);
341 if (ii != i || !performAdjustment(from_adjuster, pps.userObjectValue(i)))
342 continue;
343
344 scale = from_adjuster / pps.userObjectValue(i);
345 }
346 else
347 {
348 if (!performAdjustment(pps.userObjectValue(i), to_adjuster))
349 continue;
350
351 scale = pps.userObjectValue(i) / to_adjuster;
352 }
353
354 /* Need to scale this node */
355 dof_id_type dof = node->dof_number(sys_num, var_num, 0);
356 to_solution.set(dof, scale * to_solution(dof));
357 }
358 }
359 else
360 {
361 for (auto & elem : as_range(to_mesh.local_elements_begin(), to_mesh.local_elements_end()))
362 {
363 // Skip this element if the variable has no dofs at it.
364 if (elem->n_dofs(sys_num, var_num) < 1)
365 continue;
366
367 Real scale = 1;
368 if (_current_direction == FROM_MULTIAPP)
369 {
370 unsigned int ii = pps.nearestPointIndex(elem->vertex_average());
371 if (ii != i || !performAdjustment(from_adjuster, pps.userObjectValue(i)))
372 continue;
373
374 scale = from_adjuster / pps.userObjectValue(i);
375 }
376 else
377 {
378 if (!performAdjustment(pps.userObjectValue(i), to_adjuster))
379 continue;
380
381 scale = pps.userObjectValue(i) / to_adjuster;
382 }
383
384 dof_id_type dof = elem->dof_number(sys_num, var_num, 0);
385 to_solution.set(dof, scale * to_solution(dof));
386 }
387 }
388
389 to_solution.close();
390 to_sys.update();
391
392 // Compute the to-postprocessor again so that it has the right value with the updated solution
393 if (_current_direction == TO_MULTIAPP)
394 to_problem.computeUserObjectByName(EXEC_TRANSFER, Moose::POST_AUX, to_postprocessor);
395}

◆ declareManagedRestartableDataWithContext()

template<typename T , typename... Args>
Restartable::ManagedValue< T > Restartable::declareManagedRestartableDataWithContext ( const std::string &  data_name,
void *  context,
Args &&...  args 
)
protectedinherited

Declares a piece of "managed" restartable data and initialize it.

Here, "managed" restartable data means that the caller can destruct this data upon destruction of the return value of this method. Therefore, this ManagedValue<T> wrapper should survive after the final calls to dataStore() for it. That is... at the very end.

This is needed for objects whose destruction ordering is important, and enables natural c++ destruction in reverse construction order of the object that declares it.

See delcareRestartableData and declareRestartableDataWithContext for more information.

995 const unsigned int problem_id = std::get<0>(potential_conflict);
996 const dof_id_type dof_object_id = std::get<1>(potential_conflict);
997 const Point p = std::get<2>(potential_conflict);
998 const Real distance = std::get<3>(potential_conflict);
999
1000 // Extract target variable info
1001 auto & es = getEquationSystem(*_to_problems[problem_id], _displaced_target_mesh);
1002 System * to_sys = find_sys(es, var_name);
1003 auto var_num = to_sys->variable_number(var_name);
1004 auto & fe_type = to_sys->variable_type(var_num);
1005 bool is_nodal = _to_variables[var_index]->isNodal();
1006
1007 // Higher order elemental
1008 if (fe_type.order > CONSTANT && !is_nodal)
1009 {
1010 auto cached_distance = distance_caches[problem_id].find(p);
1011 if (cached_distance == distance_caches[problem_id].end())
1012 mooseError("Conflict point was not found in the map of all origin-target distances");
1013 // Distance is still the distance when we detected a potential overlap
1014 if (MooseUtils::absoluteFuzzyEqual(cached_distance->second, distance))
1015 overlap_found = true;
1016 }
1017 // Nodal and const monomial variable
1018 else if (MooseUtils::absoluteFuzzyEqual(
1019 dofobject_to_valsvec[problem_id].find(dof_object_id)->second.distance, distance))
1020 overlap_found = true;
1021
1022 // Map will only keep the actual overlaps
1023 if (!overlap_found)
1024 _received_conflicts.erase(conflict_it);
1025 else
1026 ++conflict_it;
1027 }
1028}

Definition at line 452 of file MultiAppTransfer.C.

453{
454 const auto extension_factor = factor - 1;
455
456 // Extend (or contract if the extension factor is negative) bounding boxes along all the
457 // directions by the same length. Greater than zero values of this member may be necessary because
458 // the nearest bounding box does not necessarily give you the closest node/element. It will depend
459 // on the partition and geometry. A node/element will more likely find its nearest source
460 // element/node by extending bounding boxes. If each of the bounding boxes covers the entire
461 // domain, a node/element will be able to find its nearest source element/node for sure, but at
462 // the same time, more communication will be involved and can be expensive.
463 for (auto & box : bboxes)
464 {
465 // libmesh set an invalid bounding box using this code
466 // for (unsigned int i=0; i<LIBMESH_DIM; i++)
467 // {
468 // this->first(i) = std::numeric_limits<Real>::max();
469 // this->second(i) = -std::numeric_limits<Real>::max();
470 // }
471 // If it is an invalid box, we should skip it
472 if (box.first(0) == std::numeric_limits<Real>::max())
473 continue;
474
475 auto width = box.second - box.first;
476 box.second += width * extension_factor;
477 box.first -= width * extension_factor;
478 }
479}

◆ getFromBoundingBoxes() [1/2]

std::vector< BoundingBox > MultiAppTransfer::getFromBoundingBoxes ( )
protectedinherited

Return the bounding boxes of all the "from" domains, including all the domains not local to this processor.

There is a boundary restricted version which will return a degenerate minimum boundary box (min, min, min, min, min, min) in the case where the source domain doesn't have any active nodes on the boundary. Note: bounding boxes are in the reference space when using coordinate transformations / positions Note: global bounding boxes are not indexed by app number. But rather outer indexing is by process, then the inner indexing is by local app number.

547 if (!at_least_one)
548 bbox.min() = max; // If we didn't hit any nodes, this will be _the_ minimum bbox
549 else
550 {
551 // Translate the bounding box to the from domain's position. We may have rotations so we must
552 // be careful in constructing the new min and max (first and second)
553 const auto from_global_num = getGlobalSourceAppIndex(i);
554 transformBoundingBox(bbox, *_from_transforms[from_global_num]);
555 }
556
557 // Cast the bounding box into a pair of points (so it can be put through
558 // MPI communication).
559 bb_points[i] = static_cast<std::pair<Point, Point>>(bbox);
560 }
561
562 // Serialize the bounding box points.
563 _communicator.allgather(bb_points);
564
565 // Recast the points back into bounding boxes and return.
566 std::vector<BoundingBox> bboxes(bb_points.size());
567 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < bb_points.size(); i++)
568 bboxes[i] = static_cast<BoundingBox>(bb_points[i]);
569
570 // possibly extend bounding boxes
571 extendBoundingBoxes(_bbox_factor, bboxes);
572
573 return bboxes;
574}

1770 // MPI communication).

538{
539 // Check which processors have apps that may include or be near this point
540 // A point may be close enough to several problems, hosted on several processes
541 bool found = false;
542
543 // Additional process-restriction techniques we could use (TODOs):
544 // - nearest_positions/_app could use its own heuristic
545 // - from_mesh_divisions could be polled for which divisions they possess on each
546 // process, depending on the behavior chosen. This could limit potential senders.
547 // This should be done ahead of this function call, for all points at once
548
549 // Select the method for determining the apps receiving points/sending values
550 if (_use_bounding_boxes)
551 {
552 // We examine all bounding boxes and find the maximum distance within a bounding box
553 // from the point. This creates a sphere around the point of interest. Any app with a bounding
554 // box that intersects this sphere (with a bboxMinDistance < nearest_max_distance) will be
555 // considered a potential source.
556 // NOTE: This is a heuristic. We could try others
557 // NOTE: from_bboxes are in the reference space, as is the point
558 Real nearest_max_distance = std::numeric_limits<Real>::max();
559 for (const auto & bbox : _from_bboxes)
560 {
561 Real distance = bboxMaxDistance(point, bbox);
562 if (distance < nearest_max_distance)
563 nearest_max_distance = distance;
564 }
565
566 unsigned int from0 = 0;
567 for (processor_id_type i_proc = 0; i_proc < n_processors();
568 from0 += _froms_per_proc[i_proc], ++i_proc)
569 for (unsigned int i_from = from0; i_from < from0 + _froms_per_proc[i_proc]; ++i_from)
570 {
571 Real distance = bboxMinDistance(point, _from_bboxes[i_from]);
572 // We will not break here because we want to send a point to all possible source domains
573 if (_greedy_search || distance <= nearest_max_distance ||
574 _from_bboxes[i_from].contains_point(point))
575 {
576 processors.insert(i_proc);
577 found = true;
578 }
579 }
580 }
581 // Greedy search will contact every single processor. It's not scalable, but if there's valid data
582 // on any subapp on any process, it will find it
583 else if (_greedy_search)
584 {
585 found = true;
586 for (const auto i_proc : make_range(n_processors()))
587 processors.insert(i_proc);
588 }
589 // Since we indicated that we only wanted values from a subapp with the same global index as the
590 // target mesh division, we might as well only communicate with the process that owns this app
591 else if (!_to_mesh_divisions.empty() &&
592 _to_mesh_division_behavior == MeshDivisionTransferUse::MATCH_SUBAPP_INDEX)
593 {
594 // The target point could have a different index in each target mesh division. So on paper, we
595 // would need to check all of them.
596 auto saved_target_div = MooseMeshDivision::INVALID_DIVISION_INDEX;
597 for (const auto i_to : index_range(_to_meshes))
598 {
599 const auto target_div = _to_mesh_divisions[i_to]->divisionIndex(
600 _to_transforms[getGlobalTargetAppIndex(i_to)]->mapBack(point));
601 // If it's the same division index, do not redo the search
602 if (target_div == saved_target_div)
603 continue;
604 else
605 saved_target_div = target_div;
606
607 // Look for the processors owning a source-app with an index equal to the target mesh division
608 for (const auto i_proc : make_range(n_processors()))
609 for (const auto i_from : make_range(_froms_per_proc[i_proc]))
610 if (target_div == _global_app_start_per_proc[i_proc] + i_from)
611 {
612 processors.insert(i_proc);
613 found = true;
614 }
615 }
616 }
617 else
618 mooseError("No algorithm were selected to find which processes may send value data "
619 "for a each target point. Please either specify using bounding boxes, "
620 "greedy search, or to_mesh_division-based parameters");
621
622 // Error out if we could not find this point when ask us to do so
623 if (!found && _error_on_miss)
624 mooseError("Cannot locate point ", point, " \n ", "mismatched meshes are used");
625}
